{"key":"processedPost-9171535","value":{"id":9171535,"first":9170875,"last":9870155,"when":1225639481,"utime":"11/02/08 05:24 PM","cleanedPost":"<blockquote>Quote:<br />The holes are about 1/4\", maybe a little smaller, and the ones below the perlite level are like 1/8\" (to keep the perlite from falling through).</blockquote><br />Which would explain the low humidity.&nbsp; The holes on the bottom need to be 1/4\" as well.&nbsp; The system works by air percolating up through the perlite and absorbing moisture as it travels.&nbsp; The holes in the bottom need to be the same size and roughly the same spacing.&nbsp; Since a 1/8 hole is only a quarter as large as a 1/4\" hole, you're not getting the intake air you need.<br />In addition, you didn't mention how you calibrated your hygrometer.<br />RR"}}